Mrs. Jordan is a 76-year-old female with recurrent colon cancer.  She had left hemicolectomy by Dr. Lee on May 13, 2008 for T2N0 sigmoid colon cancer.   Flexible sigmoidoscopy on November 15, 2010 showed a tumor at the colorectal anastomosis at 15-cm from the anal verge.  The biopsy showed no invasive adenocarcinoma.  However, the biopsy from a repeated flexible sigmoidoscopy on November 16, 2010 showed invasive moderately differentiated adenocarcinoma.  She comes to the Monona Dental Center for the surgical management on November 23, 2010.

